<p>What a great title. It's eye-catching. Here's a little more detail. You get four payment options
with this ARM. Unlike other <a href="http://www.lightning-mortgage.com/LoanTypes/ARM.htm">Hybrid ARMs</a>,
this low introductory interest rate can last for as little as
three months, after which the rate typically jumps above 4%. Still, this is less than most fixed-rate
mortgages. The objection many people have about these loans is that the rate adjusts frequently, as the
Feds adjust the short-term interest rate.</p>
<p>As home values increase, this type of loan offers you a creative way to increase your buying power.
From day one, you have more flexibility. The four payment options are:</p>

<ul><li>Fully amortized, like a 30- or 40-year fixed mortage: Make this payment each month and your loan will
be paid off in 30 or 40 years.</li>
<li>Amortized over a 15 year period: Make this payment each month and your loan will be paid off in 15 years.</li>
<li>Interest-only payment, based on the 30- or 40-year amortization: Your loan balance will be the same in 30 or 40
years as it is today if you choose this option.</li>
<li>Minimum payment, the negative amortization option. In this case, although your payment is based on an
artificial rate (say 1.95%) the difference between the real rate and the artificial rate is tacked on to
your loan amount. This means the amount you borrowed is going up rather than down.</li></ul>

<p>Why would you choose to make interest-only or minimum payments? If you knew you were selling in 5 years
or less, or you are banking on  home values appreciating. You may be playing the cash-flow game that
landlords play, too. Income less out-go equals profit.</p>
